00:01:42,859 --> 00:01:51,361
Okay, so Soft Body is this kind of chilled out but very difficult action game in which

19
00:01:51,361 --> 00:01:58,903
you control two beautiful gooey snakes at the same time.

20
00:01:59,533 --> 00:02:02,734
It's heavily influenced by a lot of action games,

21
00:02:02,734 --> 00:02:05,535
especially like shmups and twin stick shooters.

22
00:02:05,535 --> 00:02:07,056
But I tried to introduce a number of mechanics

23
00:02:07,056 --> 00:02:09,677
that are a little bit unique to action games.

24
00:02:09,677 --> 00:02:11,718
Stuff like painting the world with your body

25
00:02:11,718 --> 00:02:13,278
as opposed to shooting.

26
00:02:13,278 --> 00:02:15,379
And there's also a lot of level variation.

27
00:02:15,379 --> 00:02:18,500
So there being, as well as being like bullet hell levels

28
00:02:18,500 --> 00:02:21,782
with like tons of layers to paint and navigate through.

29
00:02:21,782 --> 00:02:25,503
There's also these sort of ethereal contemplative levels

30
00:02:25,503 --> 00:02:27,844
that have a slower vibe to them as well.

31
00:02:28,970 --> 00:02:34,473
But soft body, the thing I'm most interested in the game and the thing I'm probably most

32
00:02:34,473 --> 00:02:38,235
proud of is the split mind design mechanics that I ended up implementing into the game.

33
00:02:38,235 --> 00:02:42,798
In other words, like controlling two snakes at the same time.

34
00:02:42,798 --> 00:02:46,880
So when people first do this, it seems like it's something that's mentally impossible.

35
00:02:46,880 --> 00:02:53,064
It feels like your brain is trying to actively resist doing the thing that you want to do

36
00:02:53,064 --> 00:02:55,505
and what the game wants.

37
00:02:55,855 --> 00:03:01,397
wants you to do. It's just kind of a very challenging task. So I always felt this mechanic

38
00:03:01,397 --> 00:03:05,499
was interesting, but it actually took me a long time before I was able to wholeheartedly

39
00:03:05,499 --> 00:03:09,641
introduce it into the game. So even after I played a great game like Brothers, A Tale

40
00:03:09,641 --> 00:03:13,722
of Two Sons, which I think did an amazing job pushing this controlling two things at

41
00:03:13,722 --> 00:03:20,385
the same time mechanic, I was still a bit at a loss at how I could make it work for

42
00:03:20,385 --> 00:03:20,985
SoftBody.

43
00:03:23,592 --> 00:03:26,514
But after more than a year of gradual development,

44
00:03:26,514 --> 00:03:29,276
I fully embraced the brain splitting challenge

45
00:03:29,276 --> 00:03:31,638
of controlling these two things at the same time.

46
00:03:31,638 --> 00:03:33,820
And I ended up implementing a new mode into the game,

47
00:03:33,820 --> 00:03:36,542
the aptly named hard mode, hard game mode.

48
00:03:36,542 --> 00:03:40,485
So this hard game mode has a very high skill ceiling

49
00:03:40,485 --> 00:03:43,247
and it requires an immense amount of concentration

50
00:03:43,247 --> 00:03:45,209
from the player almost all the time they're playing.

51
00:03:45,209 --> 00:03:48,191
But designing hard game really helped me refocus

52
00:03:48,191 --> 00:03:49,732
the game's level design and fine tune

53
00:03:49,732 --> 00:03:50,953
the game's difficulty curve.

54
00:03:51,293 --> 00:03:54,814
And it really reinvigorated my work on the game,

55
00:03:54,814 --> 00:03:56,955
including, on the rest of the game,

56
00:03:56,955 --> 00:04:01,537
including like the tutorial and the introductory mode.

